Package extended_mitre.cpe

Class CPEobject

  • java.lang.Object
    • extended_mitre.cpe.CPEobject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CPEcomplexObj
    @Entity(name="cpe_ex")
public class CPEobject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a normal CPE object (vendor, product, version, ...)

    It can read from file, create objects representing CPE objects and complex CPE objects and insert them into the database

    It also can create a normal CPE object from cpe23Uri String and return it

    It can also recreate CPE match feed file from database by using the feedReconstr() method

    Author:
    Tomas Bozek (XarfNao)

      • putIntoDatabase

        public static void putIntoDatabase​(java.lang.String file,
                                   org.hibernate.SessionFactory sf)
        This method's purpose is to put basic CPE objects into database

        This method loads all basic CPE objects from the up-to-date file and puts them into database, it also calls the CPEcomplexIntoDatabase() method which puts all complex CPE objects from the up-to-date file into database with right relations between complex and basic CPE objects

        Parameters:
        file - path to .json file with CPE dictionary data (CPE match feed file)
        sf - object needed to get hibernate Session Factory and to work with database
